itz], ChessBase, May 2014.</ref>\n\n===Rapid chess===\n====Top players====\n{| class=\"wikitable center\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!  Year !! style=\"width:8%\"| January !! style=\"width:8%\"| February !! style=\"width:10%\"| March !! style=\"width:8%\"| April !! style=\"width:8%\"| May !! style=\"width:8%\"| June !! style=\"width:10%\"| July !! style=\"width:8%\"| August !! style=\"width:6%\"| September !! style=\"width:8%\"| October !! style=\"width:8%\"| November !! style=\"width:10%\"| December\n|-\n| 2014 || colspan=4 | ''N/A'' || colspan=2 | {{flagicon|United States}} [[Hikaru Nakamura]] (2841)<ref name=may2014/> || colspan=6 | {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Fabiano Caruana]] (2858)\n|-\n| 2015 || colspan=2 | {{flagicon|Italy}} [[Fabiano Caruana]] (2856)|| {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen|Carlsen]] (2855)|| colspan=7 | {{flagicon|United States}} [[Hikaru Nakamura]] (2850)|| colspan=2 | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] (2873)\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2016 || colspan=12 | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] \n|-\n| colspan=6 |  (2878) || colspan=5 | (2894) ||  (2906)\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |  2017 || colspan=12 | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] \n|-\n| colspan=6 | (2896) ||  ('''2919''') || colspan=4 | (2909) ||  (2908)\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2018  || colspan=12 | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] \n|-\n| colspan=11 | (2880)  || (2903)\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 2019 || colspan=8 align=center | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] || colspan=3 |{{flagicon|France}} [[Maxime Vachier-Lagrave]] || {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen|Carlsen]]\n|-\n| colspan=5 | (2869) || colspan=3 | (2895) || colspan=2 | (2867) || (2873)  || (2886)\n|-\n| 2020 || colspan=4 align=center | {{flagicon|Norway}} [[Magnus Carlsen]] (2881)\n|}\n\n====Top women====\n{| class=\"wikitable center\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!  Year !!  January !! February !! March !! April !! May !! June !! July !! August !! September !! October !! November !! December\n|-\n| 2014 || colspan=4 | ''N/A